 History                                                            55 1451     
 -------                                                            55 1451     
                                                                    55 1451     
 This evaluation was produced at Bettis Atomic Power Laboratory in  55 1451     
 October 2016 using the LEAPR module of NJOY2012 [1].  The phonon   55 1451     
 frequency distributions for H and Y in YH2 were calculated using   55 1451     
 the MedeA materials simulation software [2] and the alpha and      55 1451     
 beta mesh were optimized as described in Ref. 3.                   55 1451     
                                                                    55 1451     
 Theory                                                             55 1451     
 ------                                                             55 1451     
 YH2 has a fluorite type cubic crystal structure with the yttrium   55 1451     
 atoms forming a face-centered cubic sub-lattice and the hydrogen   55 1451     
 atoms situated in the tetrahedral interstices. The VASP ab initio  55 1451     
 density functional theory and PHONON lattice dynamics codes were   55 1451     
 used to calculate the phonon spectra for H and Y in YH2. The       55 1451     
 calculated 0 K lattice parameter of a=5.2032 Angstroms agrees      55 1451     
 with x-ray diffraction measurements at 90 K [4]. The calculated    55 1451     
 heat capacity agrees with measurements [5] and the calculated      55 1451     
 phonon spectra agrees with inelastic neutron scattering            55 1451     
 measurements [6,7]. The total scattering cross sections for YH2    55 1451     
 agree with measurements [8,9].                                     55 1451     
